    "abstractNote": "John bar Penkaye is one of the representatives of the East Syriac ascetical and mystical tradition. His <i>Book of the Merchant</i> was originally made up of seven centuries, but only two of them have survived. The articles provides for the first time an edition of the Syriac text, together with a French translation. The text is deliberately enigmatic but has themes in common with other of John\u2019s contemporaries and also with Evagrius Ponticus.",
